What's new in these operations:
------------------------------------

Running TRN

Kent and Rich have demonstrated TRN with multibeam running ok when passing
logged data through the system. We'll try it today in a mission context. Whether
using multibeam data works or not, we'll do several missions testing Steve's student
David's various TRN algorithm variants.

We will also do a test ROV Ventana dive. There was a major tether short that
took out the power transformer last week. Craig Dawe and Mike Burcinski will
dive into the canyon to a depth of 600-m or so. This is important for the Sur
Ridge expedition next week.

Science Plan:
------------------------------------
Testing both Mapping AUVs in preparation for the Morro Bay
expedition that sails on March 14.

Both AUVs now have SVP sensors installed that are wired through
the forward battery sphere. The driver to log these data is not complete.

Hans is trying to replace the 6046 functionality that communicates commands
to the Edgetech computer - it still doesn't work so we will continue
to run 6046 today.

The Mapping AUV 1 Edgetech system should be fixed (low frequency
sidescan was intermittent) - it seemed to be fixed during the last
TRN test day on January 25.

The Mapping AUV 2 has been apart since the Sur Ridge expedition
last September - thus we need to test all systems.

The mission defined for both AUVs includes a patch test.

Two German journalists are riding along today:
Brigitte Osterath and husband/photographer Rainer Dueckerhoff.

Science Plan:
------------------------------------
Testing both Mapping AUVs in preparation for the Morro Bay
expedition that sails on March 14.

Both AUVs now have SVP sensors installed that are wired through
the forward battery sphere.

The Mapping AUV 1 Edgetech system should be fixed (low frequency
sidescan was intermittent) - it seemed to be fixed during the last
TRN test day on January 25.

The Mapping AUV 2 has been apart since the Sur Ridge expedition
last September - thus we need to test all systems.

The mission defined for both AUVs includes a patch test.

Mapping AUV Surveys at Lucia Chica and off Morro Bay, partly in support of
possible windfarm development.

We will start with patch tests in the upper canyon, and then transit south

then deploy both Mapping AUVs for 21 hour surveys. The next pair of surveys
will be offshore Morro Bay, and two more pairs of surveys will be done between
Lucia Chica and Morro Bay. We will then recover the AMT and transit back to
Monterey Bay, ending the expedition with dual surveys on Smooth Ridge.
